    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Our review standard</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">How we handle reviews &mdash; and why.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>A real review program is worth more than a hundred fabricated stars. Every review on this page is published by the client on Clutch, an independent third-party platform, and reflects a documented engagement. We do not write, edit, or incentivize reviews, and we do not display reviews we cannot point you to at the source.</p>
      <p>We withhold an aggregate star rating until at least five verified reviews exist, because a rating built on two data points is not a meaningful average &mdash; showing one would imply more certainty than the evidence supports. When the count reaches five, an honest aggregate will appear here, sourced and dated.</p>
      <p>The verified-review program grows with each completed engagement: clients are invited &mdash; never pressured &mdash; to review the work on Clutch once it&rsquo;s delivered. If you&rsquo;d rather judge the work directly, the most useful next step is a <a href="/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review">free file review</a> &mdash; you see exactly how a Certified ProAdvisor reads your books before any money changes hands.</p>
